But at the same time, another conflict was brewing.

00:07:29.314 --> 00:07:34.684
And while the Soviet-Afghan war might have provided Osama bin Laden with the perfect training

00:07:34.694 --> 00:07:40.064
ground for a life as the head of a global terrorist organisation, and the opportunity

00:07:40.294 --> 00:07:45.904
to make his name for himself, the events of 1990 would provide him with the reason.

00:07:47.134 --> 00:07:53.134
And that reason would come on August 2nd of 1990, when Sadam Hussein’s

00:07:53.154 --> 00:07:58.454
Iraqi forces rolled into Iraq’s tiny but oil-rich neighbour, Kuwait.

00:07:59.804 --> 00:08:04.194
Within a couple of days, Kuwait had fallen, and Sadam

00:08:04.194 --> 00:08:08.274
Hussein declared that Kuwait was the 19th province of Iraq.

00:08:09.774 --> 00:08:16.554
Now, as a quick reminder of Middle Eastern geography, Iraq is directly north of Saudi Arabia,

00:08:16.874 --> 00:08:23.224
and Kuwait is located to the southeast of Iraq, sandwiched between Iraq and Saudi Arabia.

00:08:24.134 --> 00:08:28.913
So, Kuwait was taken, and there was the very real fear that Sadam

00:08:28.913 --> 00:08:33.003
Hussein might direct his forces south and take Saudi Arabia.

00:08:34.465 --> 00:08:40.393
Osama bin Laden offered his services to the Saudi rulers, the House of Saud, promising that

00:08:40.393 --> 00:08:45.683
his soldiers and money could help defend Saudi Arabia in the event of an Iraqi invasion.

00:08:46.833 --> 00:08:51.833
By this time, Osama bin Laden had made quite a reputation as a fearless

00:08:51.833 --> 00:08:56.313
fighter, and had developed a strong reputation and network in the area.

00:08:57.443 --> 00:08:59.663
But the Saudis refused.

00:09:00.063 --> 00:09:05.595
Instead, they allowed American forces to use Saudi Arabia as a launchpad

00:09:05.703 --> 00:09:09.893
for an invasion of Kuwait, in what would be called the First Gulf War.

00:09:10.963 --> 00:09:15.283
This incensed Osama bin Laden, it drove him mad.

00:09:16.053 --> 00:09:21.833
